            <div type="apparatus">
                <listApp>
                    <app>
                        <note xml:id="Job-029-fn1" type="footnote">JSul.I.04: The Karaim equivalent
                            of the standard Hebrew Job 29:1 is not included in the text, probably
                            intentionally, see Job 3:1, 4:1, etc. for similar cases. We reconstruct
                            this verse on the basis of Job 27:1 and ADub.III.84. The Hebrew text is
                            not omitted, see BHeb. <foreign xml:lang="he"
                                style="unicode-bidi: embed;">וַיֹּסֶף אִיֹּוב שְׂאֵת מְשָׁלֹו
                                וַיֹּאמַר </foreign>
                            ‘And Job answered and said’ (Job 26:1). | C: <emph>Da arttyrdy Ijov
                                kötärmä mašalyn da ajtty</emph>. | QB: <emph>Da arttyrdy Ijov
                                kötärmä mašalyn da ajtty</emph>. | ADub.III.84: <emph>Da arttyrdy
                                Ijov kötürme mašalyn da ajtty</emph>. | Kobeckaitė (2019): <emph>Da
                                arttyrdy Ijov ḱot́urḿa mašalyn da ajtty</emph>.</note>
                        <note xml:id="Job-029-fn2" type="footnote">JSul.I.04:
                                <emph>jumuščalarym</emph>; a scribal error.</note>
                        <note xml:id="Job-029-fn3" type="footnote">JSul.I.04: <emph>qulap</emph>; a
                            scribal error.</note>
                        <note xml:id="Job-029-fn4" type="footnote">An alternative translation to
                                <emph>oraɣymda</emph>, the equivalent of BHeb. <foreign
                                xml:lang="he" style="unicode-bidi: embed;">בִּקְצִירִי </foreign>
                            ‘on my branch’, written after Heb. <foreign xml:lang="he"
                                style="unicode-bidi: embed;">או </foreign>
                            ‘or’. | C: <emph>butaɣymda</emph>. | QB: <emph>butaɣymda</emph>. |
                            ADub.III.84: <emph>oraɣymda menim</emph>
                            <foreign xml:lang="he" style="unicode-bidi: embed;">או </foreign>
                            <emph>butaɣymda</emph>. | Kobeckaitė (2019):
                            <emph>butahymda</emph>.</note>
                    </app>
                </listApp>
            </div>
